commit.message:
setup.py: Release 1.0.3.

As 1.0.2 came out broken on PyPI.

directives: Mark as parallel read & write safe

I believe this feature was added to Sphinx since the initial development of
these extensions.

Currently only eager_only has been tested in parallel with Sphinx 1.8.5,
but none of the extensions have any runtime dependency on other pages
or page processing order, so should be fairly safe to mark them all
parallel read & write safe.

Also bump version to 1.0.2

MANIFEST.in: Explicitly include readme and license.

Without that, installation from PyPI was broken.

setup.py: Added support for packaging.

Source files moved to a module subfolder.
README: Mystery with doc artificats resolved, cached doctree must be removed.
README: Add "Summary" section going over what each of 3 plugins does.
search_auto_exclude: Extension to exclude files not refed by ToC from search.

modindex_exclude: PythonModuleIndex_generate() monkey-patch no longer needed.

It was first which was written, but now all required processing is done by
PyModule_run(). Not removed "just in case".

modindex_exclude: Accumulate mapping from module name to file name for excludes.

Not used currently, but may be helpful later.
eager_only: Extension to eagerly exclude content of .only:: directives.
modindex_exclude: Extension to exclude (Python) modules from indexes.
